  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The weaning rate of vasopressors drugs is usually chosen empirically by the clinician in
      critically patients. The investigators applied fuzzy logic principles to modify intravenous
      norepinephrine infusion rates during norepinephrine infusion in septic patients in order to
      reduce the duration of shock. The investigators goal was to reduce the duration of poorly
      controlled hemodynamic status.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
